{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887020377,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d7125001tX2P6v6MvozzzU","messageID":"msg_d7b1d6254001dlbUHB19DHl1Vh","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4b2095649a5141e8b35aa64aacf20507","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-035\n5: - **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n6: - **Module**: client-go\n7: - **Language**: Go\n8: - **Size**: L\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n18: \n19: The system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Go module initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** a client-go directory is created\n23: - **WHEN** `go mod init github.com/agentcube/client-go` is executed\n24: - **THEN** a go.mod file SHALL be created\n25: - **AND** the module name SHALL be github.com/agentcube/client-go\n26: - **AND** the Go version SHALL be 1.19 or higher\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Directory structure creation\n29: - **GIVEN** a Go module is initialized\n30: - **WHEN** the directory structure is created\n31: - **THEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n32: - **AND** the pkg/client directory SHALL exist\n33: - **AND** the pkg/informers directory SHALL exist\n34: - **AND** the pkg/listers directory SHALL exist\n35: \n36: ### Requirement: API types definition\n37: \n38: The system SHALL define API types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter with proper Kubernetes markers.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime type definition\n41: - **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go file\n42: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime type is defined\n43: - **THEN** the type SHALL have apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n44: - **AND** the type SHALL have kind: AgentRuntime\n45: - **AND** the type SHALL have Spec and Status fields\n46: - **AND** the type SHALL have JSON tags\n47: - **AND** the type SHALL have kubebuilder validation tags\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type definition\n50: - **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go file\n51: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter type is defined\n52: - **THEN** the type SHALL have apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n53: - **AND** the type SHALL have kind: CodeInterpreter\n54: - **AND** the type SHALL have Spec and Status fields\n55: - **AND** the type SHALL have JSON tags\n56: - **AND** the type SHALL have kubebuilder validation tags\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: API registration\n59: - **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go file\n60: - **WHEN** API types are registered\n61: - **THEN** the SchemeBuilder SHALL register AgentRuntime\n62: - **AND** the SchemeBuilder SHALL register CodeInterpreter\n63: - **AND** the GroupName SHALL be runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n64: - **AND** the SchemeGroupVersion SHALL be runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: Code generation configuration\n67: \n68: The system SHALL configure code-generator to generate client, informer, and lister code.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: client-gen configuration\n71: - **GIVEN** the Makefile with client-gen target\n72: - **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n73: - **THEN** client-gen SHALL generate clientset code\n74: - **AND** the clientset SHALL be in pkg/client/clientset/versioned\n75: - **AND** the clientset SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter clients\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: informer-gen configuration\n78: - **GIVEN** the Makefile with informer-gen target\n79: - **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n80: - **THEN** informer-gen SHALL generate informer code\n81: - **AND** the informers SHALL be in pkg/informers/externalversions\n82: - **AND** the informers SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: lister-gen configuration\n85: - **GIVEN** the Makefile with lister-gen target\n86: - **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n87: - **THEN** lister-gen SHALL generate lister code\n88: - **AND** the listers SHALL be in pkg/listers\n89: - **AND** the listers SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter listers\n90: \n91: ### Requirement: ClientSet API\n92: \n93: The system SHALL provide a complete ClientSet API for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: ClientSet initialization\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file\n97: - **WHEN** a ClientSet is created using clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags\n98: - **THEN** the ClientSet SHALL be initialized successfully\n99: - **AND** the ClientSet SHALL have a Runtime() method\n100: - **AND** the ClientSet SHALL have a Discovery() method\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Create operation\n103: - **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime object\n104: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create is called\n105: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n106: - **AND** the method SHALL return the created AgentRuntime\n107: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Get operation\n110: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n111: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get is called\n112: - **THEN** the method SHALL return the AgentRuntime object\n113: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n114: - **AND** the method SHALL return error if AgentRuntime does not exist\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime List operation\n117: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntimes\n118: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List is called\n119: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an AgentRuntimeList\n120: - **AND** the list SHALL contain all AgentRuntimes in the namespace\n121: - **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n122: - **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Update operation\n125: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n126: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update is called\n127: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n128: - **AND** the method SHALL return the updated AgentRuntime\n129: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime UpdateStatus operation\n132: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n133: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus is called\n134: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n135: - **AND** the method SHALL return the updated AgentRuntime\n136: - **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Delete operation\n139: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n140: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete is called\n141: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n142: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Watch operation\n145: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n146: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch is called\n147: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n148: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new AgentRuntimes\n149: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified AgentRuntimes\n150: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted AgentRuntimes\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime Patch operation\n153: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n154: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Patch is called\n155: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n156: - **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n157: - **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n158: - **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Create operation\n161: - **GIVEN** a valid CodeInterpreter object\n162: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create is called\n163: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n164: - **AND** the method SHALL return the created CodeInterpreter\n165: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Get operation\n168: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n169: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get is called\n170: - **THEN** the method SHALL return the CodeInterpreter object\n171: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n172: - **AND** the method SHALL return error if CodeInterpreter does not exist\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List operation\n175: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreters\n176: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List is called\n177: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a CodeInterpreterList\n178: - **AND** the list SHALL contain all CodeInterpreters in the namespace\n179: - **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n180: - **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Update operation\n183: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n184: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update is called\n185: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n186: - **AND** the method SHALL return the updated CodeInterpreter\n187: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter UpdateStatus operation\n190: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n191: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus is called\n192: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n193: - **AND** the method SHALL return the updated CodeInterpreter\n194: - **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Delete operation\n197: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n198: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete is called\n199: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n200: - **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Watch operation\n203: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n204: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Watch is called\n205: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n206: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new CodeInterpreters\n207: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified CodeInterpreters\n208: - **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted CodeInterpreters\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Patch operation\n211: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n212: - **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Patch is called\n213: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n214: - **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n215: - **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n216: - **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: Informer API\n219: \n220: The system SHALL provide informer support for event-driven workflows.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n223: - **GIVEN** a ClientSet\n224: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime informer is created\n225: - **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for AgentRuntime changes\n226: - **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n227: - **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Informer event handler registration\n230: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n231: - **WHEN** event handlers are registered\n232: - **THEN** the AddFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are added\n233: - **AND** the UpdateFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are updated\n234: - **AND** the DeleteFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are deleted\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: Informer cache synchronization\n237: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n238: - **WHEN** the informer is started\n239: - **THEN** the cache SHALL synchronize with Kubernetes\n240: - **AND** the cache SHALL contain all existing AgentRuntimes\n241: - **AND** the cache SHALL be updated on changes\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n244: - **GIVEN** a ClientSet\n245: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter informer is created\n246: - **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for CodeInterpreter changes\n247: - **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n248: - **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Lister API\n251: \n252: The system SHALL provide lister support for efficient read-only operations.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister operations\n255: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer with synchronized cache\n256: - **WHEN** the lister.List method is called\n257: - **THEN** the method SHALL return all AgentRuntimes in the cache\n258: - **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n259: - **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime namespace lister\n262: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime lister\n263: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimes(namespace) is called\n264: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a namespace-scoped lister\n265: - **AND** the namespace lister SHALL only return AgentRuntimes in that namespace\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister operations\n268: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with synchronized cache\n269: - **WHEN** the lister.List method is called\n270: - **THEN** the method SHALL return all CodeInterpreters in the cache\n271: - **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n272: - **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n275: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter lister\n276: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreters(namespace) is called\n277: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a namespace-scoped lister\n278: - **AND** the namespace lister SHALL only return CodeInterpreters in that namespace\n279: \n280: ### Requirement: Error handling\n281: \n282: The system SHALL provide proper error handling for all client operations.\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Not found error\n285: - **GIVEN** a non-existent resource name\n286: - **WHEN** a Get operation is called\n287: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n288: - **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n289: - **AND** the error status code SHALL be 404\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Already exists error\n292: - **GIVEN** an existing resource name\n293: - **WHEN** a Create operation is called with the same name\n294: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n295: - **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n296: - **AND** the error status code SHALL be 409\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Permission denied error\n299: - **GIVEN** a client with insufficient permissions\n300: - **WHEN** an operation is called\n301: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n302: - **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n303: - **AND** the error status code SHALL be 403\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Context cancellation\n306: - **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled\n307: - **WHEN** an operation is called with the cancelled context\n308: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n309: - **AND** the error SHALL be context.Canceled\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Timeout error\n312: - **GIVEN** a context with a timeout\n313: - **WHEN** an operation takes longer than the timeout\n314: - **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n315: - **AND** the error SHALL be context.DeadlineExceeded\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Type safety\n318: \n319: The system SHALL provide type-safe API access through Go types.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime type safety\n322: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime object\n323: - **WHEN** the object is passed to client methods\n324: - **THEN** the methods SHALL accept only AgentRuntime type\n325: - **AND** the methods SHALL return AgentRuntime type\n326: - **AND** compile-time type checking SHALL be enforced\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type safety\n329: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter object\n330: - **WHEN** the object is passed to client methods\n331: - **THEN** the methods SHALL accept only CodeInterpreter type\n332: - **AND** the methods SHALL return CodeInterpreter type\n333: - **AND** compile-time type checking SHALL be enforced\n334: \n335: ### Requirement: Testing\n336: \n337: The system SHALL include comprehensive tests for all functionality.\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Unit tests for client methods\n340: - **GIVEN** the client code\n341: - **WHEN** unit tests are run\n342: - **THEN** all Create, Update, Get, List, Delete methods SHALL be tested\n343: - **AND** all error cases SHALL be tested\n344: - **AND** test coverage SHALL be at least 80%\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Unit tests for informer\n347: - **GIVEN** the informer code\n348: - **WHEN** unit tests are run\n349: - **THEN** informer initialization SHALL be tested\n350: - **AND** event handling SHALL be tested\n351: - **AND** cache operations SHALL be tested\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Unit tests for lister\n354: - **GIVEN** the lister code\n355: - **WHEN** unit tests are run\n356: - **THEN** list operations SHALL be tested\n357: - **AND** namespace filtering SHALL be tested\n358: - **AND** selector filtering SHALL be tested\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Integration tests\n361: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n362: - **WHEN** integration tests are run\n363: - **THEN** all client operations SHALL be tested against real cluster\n364: - **AND** watch functionality SHALL be tested\n365: - **AND** informer synchronization SHALL be tested\n366: \n367: ### Requirement: Documentation\n368: \n369: The system SHALL include comprehensive documentation for all APIs.\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: README documentation\n372: - **GIVEN** the client-go repository\n373: - **WHEN** README.md is reviewed\n374: - **THEN** installation instructions SHALL be provided\n375: - **AND** basic usage examples SHALL be provided\n376: - **AND** API reference SHALL be provided\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: API documentation\n379: - **GIVEN** the client API\n380: - **WHEN** documentation is reviewed\n381: - **THEN** all public methods SHALL be documented\n382: - **AND** all parameters SHALL be documented\n383: - **AND** all return values SHALL be documented\n384: - **AND** error cases SHALL be documented\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: Usage examples\n387: - **GIVEN** the examples directory\n388: - **WHEN** examples are reviewed\n389: - **THEN** clientset usage examples SHALL be provided\n390: - **AND** informer usage examples SHALL be provided\n391: - **AND** lister usage examples SHALL be provided\n392: \n393: ### Requirement: Code generation automation\n394: \n395: The system SHALL automate code generation to keep it in sync with CRD definitions.\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Makefile generate target\n398: - **GIVEN** the Makefile\n399: - **WHEN** `make generate` is executed\n400: - **THEN** client-gen SHALL run\n401: - **AND** informer-gen SHALL run\n402: - **AND** lister-gen SHALL run\n403: - **AND** all generated code SHALL be up to date\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: CI code generation check\n406: - **GIVEN** a CI pipeline\n407: - **WHEN** code is committed\n408: - **THEN** the CI SHALL check if generated code is up to date\n409: - **AND** the CI SHALL fail if generated code is out of date\n410: \n411: ---\n412: \n413: ## Backward Compatibility\n414: \n415: This delta specification defines a new Go module for the client-go client library. The module provides a new API for accessing AgentCube resources and does not affect existing deployments. Existing code using direct REST API calls can continue to work, but it is recommended to migrate to the typed client for better type safety and developer experience.\n416: \n417: ## Dependencies\n418: \n419: This delta specification depends on:\n420: - Go 1.19+\n421: - Kubernetes 1.20+\n422: - AR-001: Core API definitions (CRDs)\n423: - AR-002: AgentRuntime CRD definition\n424: - AR-003: CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n425: - k8s.io/code-generator\n426: - k8s.io/client-go\n427: \n428: ## Breaking Changes\n429: \n430: None. This delta specification defines a new Go module that provides a client library. It does not break any existing functionality.\n431: \n432: ## Security Considerations\n433: \n434: 1. **Authentication**: The client shall support all Kubernetes authentication methods (kubeconfig, service account tokens, TLS certificates).\n435: 2. **Authorization**: The client shall respect Kubernetes RBAC policies and shall fail with appropriate errors when permissions are insufficient.\n436: 3. **Secret Handling**: The client shall not log sensitive information such as tokens or passwords.\n437: 4. **TLS Verification**: The client shall verify server TLS certificates by default.\n438: 5. **Context Security**: The client shall respect context cancellation and timeouts to prevent resource leaks.\n439: \n440: ## Testing Strategy\n441: \n442: ### Unit Tests\n443: - Test all client methods (Create, Update, Get, List, Delete, Watch, Patch)\n444: - Test error handling for all error cases\n445: - Test informer initialization and event handling\n446: - Test lister operations and filtering\n447: \n448: ### Integration Tests\n449: - Test all client operations against a real Kubernetes cluster\n450: - Test watch functionality with real events\n451: - Test informer synchronization\n452: - Test concurrent operations\n453: \n454: ### Performance Tests\n455: - Test CRUD operation latency\n456: - Test list operation latency with many resources\n457: - Test watch operation latency\n458: - Test informer cache synchronization time\n459: - Test memory usage with large numbers of resources\n460: \n461: ### Compatibility Tests\n462: - Test against multiple Kubernetes versions (1.20, 1.21, 1.22, 1.23, 1.24)\n463: - Test with different API server configurations\n464: - Test with different authentication methods\n\n(End of file - total 464 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-035\n- **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n- **Module**: client-go\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887020352,"end":1775887020374}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775887020404,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d7159001DapqqdEtyTTYig","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b1d6254001dlbUHB19DHl1Vh","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23354,"input":4596,"output":135,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18623}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887023430,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d7d44001JJAZQDR3bBUTa1","messageID":"msg_d7b1d7188001p66S72BGAZzKC7","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887024762,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d825700139k00ydEow76mz","messageID":"msg_d7b1d7188001p66S72BGAZzKC7","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-10a1513bf38b4524911c37704a22abb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Helm Chart templates and Values configuration for deploying the AgentCube platform components. It extends the base deployment specifications with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for all chart operations, configuration options, and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata validation\n10: \n11: The system SHALL provide a valid Helm Chart.yaml with proper metadata and version information.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml contains required metadata fields\n14: - **GIVEN** a Helm chart directory structure exists\n15: - **WHEN** the Chart.yaml file is present\n16: - **THEN** it SHALL contain fields: apiVersion, name, description, type, version, appVersion\n17: - **AND** apiVersion SHALL be set to v2\n18: - **AND** type SHALL be set to application\n19: - **AND** version SHALL follow semantic versioning (e.g., 1.0.0)\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Chart keywords and maintainers are present\n22: - **GIVEN** a valid Chart.yaml file\n23: - **WHEN** inspecting the chart metadata\n24: - **THEN** keywords SHALL include relevant terms: agentcube, ai, code-interpreter, agent-runtime\n25: - **AND** maintainers SHALL be defined with name and email fields\n26: \n27: ### Requirement: Default values.yaml structure\n28: \n29: The system SHALL provide a comprehensive default values.yaml with all configurable parameters.\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Global configuration section exists\n32: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n33: - **WHEN** reading the global configuration section\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL include: imageRegistry, imagePullSecrets, namespace, labels\n35: - **AND** imageRegistry SHALL default to empty string (allow Docker Hub)\n36: - **AND** imagePullSecrets SHALL default to empty list\n37: - **AND** namespace SHALL default to agentcube\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Controller Manager configuration exists\n40: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n41: - **WHEN** reading the controllerManager section\n42: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n43: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n44: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 2\n45: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/controller-manager\n46: - **AND** image.pullPolicy SHALL default to IfNotPresent\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration exists\n49: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n50: - **WHEN** reading the workloadManager section\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n52: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n53: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 2\n54: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/workload-manager\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Router configuration exists\n57: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n58: - **WHEN** reading the router section\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n60: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n61: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 3\n62: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/router\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: RBAC configuration exists\n65: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n66: - **WHEN** reading the rbac section\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL include: create field\n68: - **AND** create SHALL default to true\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Monitoring configuration exists\n71: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n72: - **WHEN** reading the monitoring section\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled and serviceMonitor fields\n74: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to false\n75: - **AND** serviceMonitor.enabled SHALL default to false\n76: - **AND** serviceMonitor.interval SHALL default to 30s\n77: - **AND** serviceMonitor.scrapeTimeout SHALL default to 10s\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Security contexts are configured\n80: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n81: - **WHEN** reading the security context sections\n82: - **THEN** podSecurityContext SHALL include: runAsNonRoot, runAsUser, fsGroup\n83: - **AND** runAsNonRoot SHALL default to true\n84: - **AND** runAsUser SHALL default to 1000\n85: - **AND** containerSecurityContext SHALL include: allowPrivilegeEscalation, capabilities, readOnlyRootFilesystem\n86: - **AND** allowPrivilegeEscalation SHALL default to false\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: CRD template installation\n89: \n90: The system SHALL install Custom Resource Definitions as part of the Helm chart.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: CRD templates exist in correct location\n93: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates directory\n94: - **WHEN** listing the templates/crds/ directory\n95: - **THEN** agentruntime.yaml SHALL be present\n96: - **AND** codeinterpreter.yaml SHALL be present\n97: - **AND** CRD templates SHALL use helm.sh/resource-policy: keep annotation\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: CRDs install with correct metadata\n100: - **GIVEN** a Helm install command is executed\n101: - **WHEN** the CRD templates are rendered and applied\n102: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n103: - **AND** version SHALL be v1alpha1\n104: - **AND** scope SHALL be Namespaced\n105: - **AND** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: CRDs support version upgrades\n108: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentCube CRD installation\n109: - **WHEN** upgrading to a new chart version with CRD changes\n110: - **THEN** the CRDs SHALL be updated using helm.sh/hook: crd-install\n111: - **AND** existing CRD instances SHALL be preserved during upgrade\n112: - **AND** the upgrade SHALL not break existing resources\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Controller Manager deployment template\n115: \n116: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Controller Manager component.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Controller Manager Deployment renders correctly\n119: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/deployment.yaml template\n120: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n121: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named agentcube-controller-manager\n122: - **AND** replicas SHALL match controllerManager.replicaCount from values\n123: - **AND** the container SHALL use the image specified in values\n124: - **AND** imagePullPolicy SHALL match the configured value\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Controller Manager Service is created\n127: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/service.yaml template\n128: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n129: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be named agentcube-controller-manager\n130: - **AND** the Service type SHALL match controllerManager.service.type\n131: - **AND** the Service port SHALL match controllerManager.service.port\n132: - **AND** the Service SHALL target port 8080\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Controller Manager ServiceAccount is created\n135: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml template\n136: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with rbac.create=true\n137: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount SHALL be created for the Controller Manager\n138: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have appropriate labels\n139: - **AND** the Deployment SHALL use this ServiceAccount\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Controller Manager disabled via values\n142: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with controllerManager.enabled=false\n143: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n144: - **THEN** Controller Manager Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n145: - **AND** Controller Manager Service SHALL NOT be created\n146: - **AND** Controller Manager ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment template\n149: \n150: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Workload Manager component.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment renders correctly\n153: - **GIVEN** the workload-manager/deployment.yaml template\n154: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n155: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named workloadmanager\n156: - **AND** replicas SHALL match workloadManager.replicaCount from values\n157: - **AND** the container SHALL expose HTTP on port 8080\n158: - **AND** liveness and readiness probes SHALL be configured\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Workload Manager health checks are configured\n161: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager Deployment template\n162: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n163: - **THEN** livenessProbe SHALL be configured with HTTP GET /health\n164: - **AND** readinessProbe SHALL be configured with HTTP GET /health\n165: - **AND** both probes SHALL use port 8080\n166: - **AND** initialDelaySeconds SHALL be 10\n167: - **AND** periodSeconds SHALL be 10\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Service is created\n170: - **GIVEN** the workload-manager/service.yaml template\n171: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n172: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be named workloadmanager\n173: - **AND** the Service type SHALL be ClusterIP\n174: - **AND** the Service SHALL expose port matching values configuration\n175: - **AND** the Service SHALL select pods with correct labels\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Workload Manager disabled via values\n178: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with workloadManager.enabled=false\n179: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n180: - **THEN** Workload Manager Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n181: - **AND** Workload Manager Service SHALL NOT be created\n182: - **AND** Workload Manager ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Router deployment template\n185: \n186: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Router component.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Router Deployment renders correctly\n189: - **GIVEN** the router/deployment.yaml template\n190: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n191: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named agentcube-router\n192: - **AND** replicas SHALL match router.replicaCount from values\n193: - **AND** the container SHALL expose HTTP on port 8080\n194: - **AND** container args SHALL include --port=<targetPort> and --debug\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Router configures Workload Manager URL\n197: - **GIVEN** the Router Deployment template\n198: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered in namespace N\n199: - **THEN** the Router pod SHALL have WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable\n200: - **AND** WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL SHALL be set to http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P\n201: - **AND** P SHALL be the Workload Manager service port from values\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Router Service supports multiple types\n204: - **GIVEN** the router/service.yaml template\n205: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with router.service.type=LoadBalancer\n206: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be of type LoadBalancer\n207: - **AND** the Service SHALL be named agentcube-router\n208: - **AND** externalTrafficPolicy SHALL be set to Local (if applicable)\n209: - **AND** annotations SHALL be preserved from values\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Router disabled via values\n212: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with router.enabled=false\n213: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n214: - **THEN** Router Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n215: - **AND** Router Service SHALL NOT be created\n216: - **AND** Router ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: RBAC resources creation\n219: \n220: The system SHALL create appropriate RBAC resources for all components when enabled.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole is created\n223: - **GIVEN** rbac.create=true in values\n224: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n225: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n226: - **AND** a ClusterRole named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n227: - **AND** a ClusterRoleBinding named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n228: - **AND** the Binding SHALL tie the ServiceAccount to the ClusterRole\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole has required permissions\n231: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager ClusterRole template\n232: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n233: - **THEN** rules SHALL include permissions for agent-sandbox resources\n234: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for AgentCube runtime CRDs\n235: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for core workloads (pods, deployments)\n236: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for auth (tokenreviews)\n237: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for secrets\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Router RBAC is optional\n240: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with router.rbac.create=true\n241: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n242: - **THEN** Router ServiceAccount SHALL be created\n243: - **AND** Router Role SHALL be created in the release namespace\n244: - **AND** Router RoleBinding SHALL be created\n245: - **AND** the Role SHALL allow verbs on secrets in that namespace\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: RBAC disabled via values\n248: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with rbac.create=false\n249: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n250: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be created\n251: - **AND** Deployments SHALL use default ServiceAccount\n252: \n253: ### Requirement: Resource limits and requests\n254: \n255: The system SHALL support configurable resource limits and requests for all components.\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Default resources are applied\n258: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml with resource specifications\n259: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n260: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have resource requests\n261: - **AND** requests.cpu SHALL be 100m by default\n262: - **AND** requests.memory SHALL be 128Mi by default\n263: - **AND** limits.cpu SHALL be 500m by default\n264: - **AND** limits.memory SHALL be 512Mi by default\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Custom resources override defaults\n267: - **GIVEN** custom values.yaml with custom resource specifications\n268: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with custom values\n269: - **THEN** resource requests SHALL match the custom values\n270: - **AND** resource limits SHALL match the custom values\n271: - **AND** default values SHALL be overridden\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Resources can be disabled\n274: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with empty resource sections\n275: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n276: - **THEN** containers SHALL NOT have resource requests\n277: - **AND** containers SHALL NOT have resource limits\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Node selectors and affinity\n280: \n281: The system SHALL support node selectors and affinity rules for pod scheduling.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Node selectors are applied\n284: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with nodeSelector configuration\n285: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n286: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified nodeSelector\n287: - **AND** pods SHALL only schedule on matching nodes\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Tolerations are applied\n290: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with tolerations configuration\n291: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n292: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified tolerations\n293: - **AND** pods SHALL be able to schedule on tainted nodes\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Affinity rules are applied\n296: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with affinity configuration\n297: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n298: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified affinity rules\n299: - **AND** podAntiAffinity rules SHALL be respected during scheduling\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: High availability configuration\n302: \n303: The system SHALL support high availability through replica count and anti-affinity configuration.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Multiple replicas are scheduled\n306: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with controllerManager.replicaCount=3\n307: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n308: - **THEN** the Controller Manager Deployment SHALL have 3 replicas\n309: - **AND** 3 pods SHALL be scheduled (subject to resource availability)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Pod anti-affinity prevents single node failure\n312: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with podAntiAffinity configuration\n313: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n314: - **THEN** pods SHALL have anti-affinity rules configured\n315: - **AND** pods SHALL prefer to run on different nodes\n316: - **AND** pod disruption budget SHALL prevent single node failures\n317: \n318: ### Requirement: Monitoring integration\n319: \n320: The system SHALL support optional Prometheus monitoring through ServiceMonitor resources.\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor is not created by default\n323: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with monitoring.enabled=false (default)\n324: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n325: - **THEN** no ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor is created when enabled\n328: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with monitoring.enabled=true and serviceMonitor.enabled=true\n329: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n330: - **THEN** ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created for each enabled component\n331: - **AND** ServiceMonitor interval SHALL match values configuration\n332: - **AND** ServiceMonitor scrapeTimeout SHALL match values configuration\n333: - **AND** ServiceMonitor SHALL select pods with appropriate labels\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor labels are configurable\n336: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with custom serviceMonitor labels\n337: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n338: - **THEN** ServiceMonitor SHALL have the specified labels\n339: - **AND** Prometheus SHALL discover the ServiceMonitor based on labels\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Image pull secrets and registry configuration\n342: \n343: The system SHALL support configuring image registry and pull secrets.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Global image registry is applied\n346: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global.imageRegistry=registry.example.com\n347: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n348: - **THEN** all component images SHALL use the registry.example.com prefix\n349: - **AND** image references SHALL be formatted as registry.example.com/component:tag\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Image pull secrets are configured\n352: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global.imagePullSecrets=[my-secret]\n353: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n354: - **THEN** all component ServiceAccounts SHALL have imagePullSecrets\n355: - **AND** the secret my-secret SHALL be referenced\n356: - **AND** multiple secrets SHALL be supported\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Component-specific image tags override global\n359: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global image configuration and component-specific tags\n360: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n361: - **THEN** component-specific image tags SHALL take precedence over global settings\n362: - **AND** each component SHALL use its configured tag\n363: \n364: ### Requirement: Development environment configuration\n365: \n366: The system SHALL provide a values-dev.yaml file for development deployments.\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: Dev values use minimal resources\n369: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n370: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n371: - **THEN** component replicaCounts SHALL be 1\n372: - **AND** resource requests SHALL be minimal (e.g., 50m cpu, 64Mi memory)\n373: - **AND** resource limits SHALL be conservative\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Dev values disable monitoring\n376: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n377: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n378: - **THEN** monitoring SHALL be disabled\n379: - **AND** no ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Dev values allow insecure configurations\n382: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n383: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n384: - **THEN** security contexts MAY be relaxed for development\n385: - **AND** debug flags MAY be enabled\n386: \n387: ### Requirement: Production environment configuration\n388: \n389: The system SHALL provide a values-prod.yaml file for production deployments.\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Prod values use high availability configuration\n392: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n393: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n394: - **THEN** Controller Manager replicaCount SHALL be 2 or more\n395: - **AND** Workload Manager replicaCount SHALL be 2 or more\n396: - **AND** Router replicaCount SHALL be 3 or more\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Prod values enable monitoring\n399: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n400: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n401: - **THEN** monitoring SHALL be enabled\n402: - **AND** ServiceMonitor SHALL be created\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Prod values configure pod anti-affinity\n405: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n406: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n407: - **THEN** podAntiAffinity rules SHALL be configured\n408: - **AND** pods SHALL prefer different nodes\n409: - **AND** PodDisruptionBudget SHALL be configured\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: Prod values use production resources\n412: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n413: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n414: - **THEN** resource requests SHALL be appropriate for production load\n415: - **AND** resource limits SHALL be configured to prevent resource exhaustion\n416: \n417: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation workflow\n418: \n419: The system SHALL support standard Helm installation, upgrade, and rollback workflows.\n420: \n421: #### Scenario: Fresh install with default values\n422: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3\n423: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube --namespace agentcube --create-namespace`\n424: - **THEN** all CRDs SHALL be installed\n425: - **AND** all enabled components SHALL be deployed\n426: - **AND** all Services SHALL be created\n427: - **AND** all RBAC resources SHALL be created\n428: - **AND** pods SHALL become ready within reasonable time\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Install with custom values file\n431: - **GIVEN** a custom values file custom-values.yaml\n432: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube -f custom-values.yaml`\n433: - **THEN** the installation SHALL use the custom values\n434: - **AND** all customizations SHALL be applied\n435: - **AND** default values SHALL be overridden where specified\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Install with inline values\n438: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart\n439: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube --set controllerManager.replicaCount=5`\n440: - **THEN** the Controller Manager SHALL use 5 replicas\n441: - **AND** other components SHALL use default values\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: Upgrade preserves existing configuration\n444: - **GIVEN** an existing Helm installation\n445: - **WHEN** running `helm upgrade agentcube ./agentcube`\n446: - **THEN** existing resources SHALL be updated in-place\n447: - **AND** persistent data SHALL be preserved\n448: - **AND** pods SHALL be restarted gracefully\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Rollback restores previous version\n451: - **GIVEN** a Helm installation that has been upgraded\n452: - **WHEN** running `helm rollback agentcube`\n453: - **THEN** the chart SHALL be restored to the previous version\n454: - **AND** all resources SHALL be reverted to previous state\n455: - **AND** the rollback SHALL not cause downtime\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: Uninstall removes all resources\n458: - **GIVEN** an existing Helm installation\n459: - **WHEN** running `helm uninstall agentcube`\n460: - **THEN** all Deployments SHALL be deleted\n461: - **AND** all Services SHALL be deleted\n462: - **AND** all RBAC resources SHALL be deleted\n463: - **AND** CRDs SHALL be kept (due to resource-policy: keep annotation)\n464: \n465: ### Requirement: Chart documentation\n466: \n467: The system SHALL provide comprehensive documentation for the Helm chart.\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: README.md contains installation instructions\n470: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart README.md file\n471: - **WHEN** reading the documentation\n472: - **THEN** it SHALL contain installation instructions\n473: - **AND** it SHALL describe all configuration options\n474: - **AND** it SHALL provide example values files\n475: - **AND** it SHALL include troubleshooting guidance\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: values.yaml has inline comments\n478: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n479: - **WHEN** inspecting the values\n480: - **THEN** each configuration section SHALL have descriptive comments\n481: - **AND** important parameters SHALL be documented\n482: - **AND** default values SHALL be explained\n483: \n484: #### Scenario: NOTES.txt provides post-install information\n485: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates/NOTES.txt file\n486: - **WHEN** an installation completes\n487: - **THEN** useful information SHALL be displayed\n488: - **AND** the information SHALL include: how to access services, how to check status, next steps\n489: \n490: ### Requirement: Template validation and linting\n491: \n492: The system SHALL provide valid templates that pass Helm linting.\n493: \n494: #### Scenario: Chart passes helm lint\n495: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart directory\n496: - **WHEN** running `helm lint ./agentcube`\n497: - **THEN** the linting SHALL pass without errors\n498: - **AND** no warnings SHALL be raised\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Chart passes helm template render\n501: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart directory\n502: - **WHEN** running `helm template test ./agentcube`\n503: - **THEN** the template SHALL render successfully\n504: - **AND** valid YAML SHALL be produced\n505: - **AND** no rendering errors SHALL occur\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: Chart syntax is valid\n508: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates\n509: - **WHEN** validating Go template syntax\n510: - **THEN** all templates SHALL have valid syntax\n511: - **AND** all variables SHALL be properly referenced\n512: - **AND** all conditionals SHALL be properly formatted\n513: \n514: ---\n515: \n516: ## Backward Compatibility\n517: \n518: This delta specification introduces new Helm Chart functionality without breaking changes to existing deployment methods. The Helm chart is an additional deployment option that can coexist with existing manual YAML deployment approaches.\n519: \n520: ## Dependencies\n521: \n522: This delta specification depends on:\n523: - Kubernetes 1.20+ (as specified in base requirements)\n524: - Helm 3.0+ for chart installation and management\n525: - Base deployment specifications: `deployment/spec.md`\n526: - Existing CRD definitions: `config/crd/bases/`\n527: - Base component configurations from `deployment/spec.md`\n528: \n529: ## Breaking Changes\n530: \n531: None. This delta specification defines a new Helm Chart deployment mechanism that provides an alternative to existing deployment methods without introducing breaking changes to existing functionality or APIs.\n532: \n533: ## Security Considerations\n534: \n535: 1. **RBAC Permissions**: The chart creates RBAC resources with minimal required permissions following the principle of least privilege\n536: 2. **Secrets Management**: The chart supports pulling images from private registries using image pull secrets without storing secrets in values files\n537: 3. **Security Contexts**: The chart applies non-root user, read-only filesystem, and dropped capabilities by default\n538: 4. **Network Policies**: While not explicitly required in this spec, the chart should support network policy configuration for pod-to-pod communication\n539: 5. **Image Security**: The chart supports image pull policy configuration and private registry authentication\n540: \n541: ## Testing Strategy\n542: \n543: ### Template Tests\n544: - Verify all templates render correctly with default values\n545: - Verify all templates render correctly with custom values\n546: - Verify templates fail gracefully with invalid values\n547: - Verify CRD templates install and upgrade correctly\n548: \n549: ### Installation Tests\n550: - Test fresh installation with default values\n551: - Test installation with custom values files\n552: - Test installation with inline value overrides\n553: - Verify all resources are created correctly\n554: - Verify pods become ready and services are accessible\n555: \n556: ### Upgrade Tests\n557: - Test upgrade from one chart version to another\n558: - Verify existing resources are updated in-place\n559: - Verify data persistence during upgrades\n560: - Verify no downtime during upgrades\n561: \n562: ### Rollback Tests\n563: - Test rollback to previous chart version\n564: - Verify resources are restored to previous state\n565: - Verify no data loss during rollback\n566: \n567: ### Multi-Environment Tests\n568: - Test deployment with values-dev.yaml\n569: - Test deployment with values-prod.yaml\n570: - Verify environment-specific configurations are applied\n571: \n572: ### Integration Tests\n573: - Test interaction between components (Router → Workload Manager)\n574: - Verify service discovery works correctly\n575: - Test RBAC permissions are correct\n576: - Verify CRDs can be created and managed\n577: \n578: ### Validation Tests\n579: - Run `helm lint` to verify chart syntax\n580: - Run `helm template` to verify rendering\n581: - Verify Chart.yaml follows Helm best practices\n582: - Verify values.yaml is properly structured and documented\n\n(End of file - total 582 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Helm Chart templates and Values configuration for deploying the AgentCube platform components. It extends the base deployment specifications with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for all chart operations, configuration options, and lifecycle management.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a valid Helm Chart.yaml with proper metadata and version information.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml contains required metadata fields\n- **GIVEN** a Helm chart directory structure exists\n- **WHEN** the Chart.yaml file is present\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain fields: apiVersion, name, description, type, version, appVersion\n- **AND** apiVersion SHALL be set to v2\n- **AND** type SHALL be set to application\n- **AND** version SHALL follow semantic versioning (e.g., 1.0.0)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887024751,"end":1775887024759}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775887024787,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d8279001g5tIydlergRx9L","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b1d7188001p66S72BGAZzKC7","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29290,"input":5953,"output":106,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":23231}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887030117,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d9764001IOziUTDWRee1vI","messageID":"msg_d7b1d82a8001Koc4IWBrwV1H6y","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887185670,"sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1ff584001tNh6XSYwwGp136","messageID":"msg_d7b1d82a8001Koc4IWBrwV1H6y","sessionID":"ses_284e2b9b0ffeTLz487gUEGJpwI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-54660ae0376f4c079edfdceba549090a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-035\n- **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n- **Module**: client-go\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n\n#### Scenario: Go module initialization with correct path\n- **GIVEN** a client-go directory is created\n- **WHEN** `go mod init github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` is executed\n- **THEN** a go.mod file SHALL be created\n- **AND** the module name SHALL be github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n- **AND** the Go version SHALL be 1.19 or higher\n\n#### Scenario: Directory structure creation\n- **GIVEN** a Go module is initialized\n- **WHEN** the directory structure is created\n- **THEN** the clientset/versioned directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the clientset/versioned/scheme directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the clientset/versioned/fake directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the informers/externalversions directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n\n### Requirement: Clientset Interface and Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete Clientset interface and implementation with proper constructors.\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset Interface definition\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/clientset.go file\n- **WHEN** the Interface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have a Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface method\n- **AND** it SHALL have a RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface method\n- **AND** the interface SHALL be complete\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset struct with embedded discovery client\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/clientset.go file\n- **WHEN** the Clientset struct is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL embed *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n- **AND** it SHALL hold runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfig constructor\n- **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config\n- **WHEN** NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return (*Clientset, error)\n- **AND** the Clientset SHALL be properly initialized\n- **AND** error SHALL be nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfigAndClient constructor\n- **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config and *http.Client\n- **WHEN** NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return (*Clientset, error)\n- **AND** the Clientset SHALL use the provided HTTP client\n- **AND** error SHALL be nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie constructor\n- **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config\n- **WHEN** NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return *Clientset\n- **AND** it SHALL panic on error\n- **AND** the Clientset SHALL be properly initialized\n\n#### Scenario: New constructor with REST client\n- **GIVEN** a valid rest.Interface\n- **WHEN** New(c rest.Interface) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return *Clientset\n- **AND** the Clientset SHALL use the provided REST client\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1 group accessor\n- **GIVEN** a Clientset instance\n- **WHEN** RuntimeV1alpha1() is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n- **AND** the returned interface SHALL be properly initialized\n\n### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1 Typed Client\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete typed client for the runtime.v1alpha1 API group.\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface definition\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go file\n- **WHEN** the RuntimeV1alpha1Interface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have a RESTClient() rest.Interface method\n- **AND** it SHALL embed AgentRuntimesGetter\n- **AND** it SHALL embed CodeInterpretersGetter\n- **AND** the interface SHALL be complete\n\n#### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Client with proper REST configuration\n- **GIVEN** the RuntimeV1alpha1Client struct\n- **WHEN** it is instantiated\n- **THEN** GroupVersion SHALL be pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion\n- **AND** APIPath SHALL be /apis\n- **AND** it SHALL use negotiated serializer from clientset/versioned/scheme\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimesGetter interface\n- **GIVEN** the RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimesGetter is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have an AgentRuntimes(namespace string) method\n- **AND** the method SHALL return AgentRuntimeInterface\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface with full CRUD operations\n- **GIVEN** the agentruntime.go file\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeInterface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have Create(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Update(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have UpdateStatus(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Delete(ctx, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n- **AND** it SHALL have DeleteCollection(ctx, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n- **AND** it SHALL have Get(ctx, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have List(ctx, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Watch(ctx, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Patch(ctx, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL embed AgentRuntimeExpansion\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime REST resource plural\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime typed client\n- **WHEN** inspecting the REST resource configuration\n- **THEN** the resource plural SHALL be agentruntimes\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n- **GIVEN** the RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpretersGetter is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have a CodeInterpreters(namespace string) method\n- **AND** the method SHALL return CodeInterpreterInterface\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInterface with full CRUD operations\n- **GIVEN** the codeinterpreter.go file\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreterInterface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have Create(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Update(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have UpdateStatus(ctx, *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Delete(ctx, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n- **AND** it SHALL have DeleteCollection(ctx, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n- **AND** it SHALL have Get(ctx, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have List(ctx, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Watch(ctx, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL have Patch(ctx, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n- **AND** it SHALL embed CodeInterpreterExpansion\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter REST resource plural\n- **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter typed client\n- **WHEN** inspecting the REST resource configuration\n- **THEN** the resource plural SHALL be codeinterpreters\n\n### Requirement: Expansion Hooks\n\nThe system SHALL provide expansion hooks for custom methods.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeExpansion interface\n- **GIVEN** the generated_expansion.go file\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeExpansion interface is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface\n- **AND** it SHALL be reserved for custom methods\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterExpansion interface\n- **GIVEN** the generated_expansion.go file\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreterExpansion interface is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface\n- **AND** it SHALL be reserved for custom methods\n\n### Requirement: Fake Clients\n\nThe system SHALL provide fake clients for testing.\n\n#### Scenario: Fake runtime client\n- **GIVEN** the fake_runtime_client.go file\n- **WHEN** the FakeRuntimeV1alpha1Client is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n- **AND** it SHALL provide in-memory storage\n- **AND** it SHALL support testing scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Fake AgentRuntime client\n- **GIVEN** the fake_agentruntime.go file\n- **WHEN** the FakeAgentRuntimes struct is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement AgentRuntimeInterface\n- **AND** it SHALL provide Add, Update, Get, List methods\n- **AND** it SHALL support test assertions\n\n#### Scenario: Fake CodeInterpreter client\n- **GIVEN** the fake_codeinterpreter.go file\n- **WHEN** the FakeCodeInterpreters struct is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL implement CodeInterpreterInterface\n- **AND** it SHALL provide Add, Update, Get, List methods\n- **AND** it SHALL support test assertions\n\n### Requirement: Scheme and Codecs\n\nThe system SHALL provide proper scheme registration for the generated types.\n\n#### Scenario: SchemeBuilder with API types\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go file\n- **WHEN** the SchemeBuilder is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL register runtime/v1alpha1 types\n- **AND** it SHALL provide AddToScheme function\n- **AND** the Scheme SHALL be properly initialized\n\n#### Scenario: Codecs and ParameterCodec\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go file\n- **WHEN** codecs are created\n- **THEN** a Scheme SHALL be built\n- **AND** Codecs SHALL be created from the Scheme\n- **AND** ParameterCodec SHALL be created from the Scheme\n\n### Requirement: Informer Factory\n\nThe system SHALL provide a SharedInformerFactory for managing informers.\n\n#### Scenario: SharedInformerFactory interface\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/factory.go file\n- **WHEN** the SharedInformerFactory interface is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL embed internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n- **AND** it SHALL have Start(stopCh <-chan struct{}) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Shutdown() method\n- **AND** it SHALL have WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool method\n- **AND** it SHALL have ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface method\n\n#### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactory constructor\n- **GIVEN** a versioned.Interface and defaultResync time.Duration\n- **WHEN** NewSharedInformerFactory(client, defaultResync) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return SharedInformerFactory\n- **AND** the factory SHALL use the provided client\n- **AND** the factory SHALL use the provided resync duration\n\n#### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions constructor\n- **GIVEN** a versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, and options\n- **WHEN** NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options...) is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return SharedInformerFactory\n- **AND** WithCustomResyncConfig option SHALL be supported\n- **AND** WithTweakListOptions option SHALL be supported\n- **AND** WithNamespace option SHALL be supported\n- **AND** WithTransform option SHALL be supported\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime group interface\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go file\n- **WHEN** the Interface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have V1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface method\n- **AND** New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions) SHALL return the interface\n\n#### Scenario: V1alpha1 version interface\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go file\n- **WHEN** the Interface type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have AgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer method\n- **AND** it SHALL have CodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer method\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInformer interface\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go file\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeInformer type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister method\n- **AND** NewAgentRuntimeInformer factory function SHALL be provided\n- **AND** NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer factory function SHALL be provided\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInformer interface\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go file\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreterInformer type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister method\n- **AND** NewCodeInterpreterInformer factory function SHALL be provided\n- **AND** NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer factory function SHALL be provided\n\n#### Scenario: Generic resource routing\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/generic.go file\n- **WHEN** ForResource is called\n- **THEN** v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\") SHALL route to AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n- **AND** v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\") SHALL route to CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n\n#### Scenario: Internal factory interfaces\n- **GIVEN** the informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go file\n- **WHEN** the interfaces are defined\n- **THEN** NewInformerFunc SHALL be defined as func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n- **AND** SharedInformerFactory SHALL have Start and InformerFor methods\n- **AND** TweakListOptionsFunc SHALL be defined as func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n\n### Requirement: Listers\n\nThe system SHALL provide efficient listers for read-only access.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go file\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeLister type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister method\n- **AND** it SHALL embed AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n- **AND** NewAgentRuntimeLister SHALL use runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntimeLister\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL embed AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go file\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreterLister type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister method\n- **AND** it SHALL embed CodeInterpreterListerExpansion\n- **AND** NewCodeInterpreterLister SHALL use runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister interface\n- **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreterLister\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister type is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL have List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL have Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) method\n- **AND** it SHALL embed CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion\n\n#### Scenario: Lister expansion interfaces\n- **GIVEN** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go file\n- **WHEN** the expansion interfaces are defined\n- **THEN** AgentRuntimeListerExpansion SHALL be an empty interface\n- **AND** AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion SHALL be an empty interface\n- **AND** CodeInterpreterListerExpansion SHALL be an empty interface\n- **AND** CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion SHALL be an empty interface\n\n### Requirement: Fake Clientset\n\nThe system SHALL provide a fake clientset for testing.\n\n#### Scenario: NewSimpleClientset constructor\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go file\n- **WHEN** NewSimpleClientset() is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return *fake.Clientset\n- **AND** the clientset SHALL provide in-memory storage\n- **AND** the clientset SHALL support test assertions\n\n#### Scenario: Fake scheme registration\n- **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/fake/register.go file\n- **WHEN** the fake scheme is registered\n- **THEN** it SHALL register all runtime/v1alpha1 types\n- **AND** it SHALL provide AddToScheme function\n\n### Requirement: ClientSet Usage Scenarios\n\nThe system SHALL provide complete client operations for all resource types.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Create operation\n- **GIVEN** a valid *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, agentRuntime, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the created *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Get operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime object\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if AgentRuntime does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime List operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntimes\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List(ctx, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList\n- **AND** the list SHALL contain all AgentRuntimes in the namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Update operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, agentRuntime, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime UpdateStatus operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Delete operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime DeleteCollection operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntimes\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).DeleteCollection(ctx, opts, listOpts) is called\n- **THEN** the matching AgentRuntimes SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support selector-based deletion\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Watch operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch(ctx, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted AgentRuntimes\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Patch operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Patch(ctx, name, pt, data, opts, subresources...) is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Create operation\n- **GIVEN** a valid *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the created *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Get operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter object\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if CodeInterpreter does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreters\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List(ctx, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList\n- **AND** the list SHALL contain all CodeInterpreters in the namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Update operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update(ctx, codeInterpreter, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter UpdateStatus operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Delete operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter DeleteCollection operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreters\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).DeleteCollection(ctx, opts, listOpts) is called\n- **THEN** the matching CodeInterpreters SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support selector-based deletion\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Watch operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Watch(ctx, opts) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new CodeInterpreters\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified CodeInterpreters\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted CodeInterpreters\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Patch operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Patch(ctx, name, pt, data, opts, subresources...) is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n\n### Requirement: Informer Usage Scenarios\n\nThe system SHALL provide complete informer functionality for event-driven workflows.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n- **GIVEN** a ClientSet and SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes() is called\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for AgentRuntime changes\n- **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n- **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n\n#### Scenario: Informer event handler registration\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n- **WHEN** event handlers are registered using AddEventHandler\n- **THEN** the OnAdd function SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are added\n- **AND** the OnUpdate function SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are updated\n- **AND** the OnDelete function SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Informer cache synchronization\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n- **WHEN** factory.Start(stopCh) and factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh) are called\n- **THEN** the cache SHALL synchronize with Kubernetes\n- **AND** the cache SHALL contain all existing AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the cache SHALL be updated on changes\n- **AND** WaitForCacheSync SHALL return true when synchronized\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n- **GIVEN** a ClientSet and SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters() is called\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for CodeInterpreter changes\n- **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n- **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n\n#### Scenario: Informer shutdown\n- **GIVEN** a running informer factory\n- **WHEN** factory.Shutdown() is called\n- **THEN** all informers SHALL stop watching\n- **AND** resources SHALL be cleaned up\n- **AND** the factory SHALL be safe to re-create\n\n### Requirement: Lister Usage Scenarios\n\nThe system SHALL provide efficient lister operations for read-only access.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister list all\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer with synchronized cache\n- **WHEN** lister.List(labels.Everything()) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return all AgentRuntimes in the cache\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister namespace scoped\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime lister\n- **WHEN** lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).List(labels.Everything()) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return only AgentRuntimes in that namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime namespace lister get\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime namespace lister\n- **WHEN** namespaceLister.Get(name) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if not found\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister list all\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with synchronized cache\n- **WHEN** lister.List(labels.Everything()) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return all CodeInterpreters in the cache\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister namespace scoped\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter lister\n- **WHEN** lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).List(labels.Everything()) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return only CodeInterpreters in that namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister get\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n- **WHEN** namespaceLister.Get(name) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if not found\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling\n\nThe system SHALL provide proper error handling for all client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Not found error\n- **GIVEN** a non-existent resource name\n- **WHEN** a Get operation is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 404\n\n#### Scenario: Already exists error\n- **GIVEN** an existing resource name\n- **WHEN** a Create operation is called with the same name\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 409\n\n#### Scenario: Permission denied error\n- **GIVEN** a client with insufficient permissions\n- **WHEN** an operation is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 403\n\n#### Scenario: Context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled\n- **WHEN** an operation is called with the cancelled context\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be context.Canceled\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout error\n- **GIVEN** a context with a timeout\n- **WHEN** an operation takes longer than the timeout\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be context.DeadlineExceeded\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid patch type\n- **GIVEN** an invalid patch type\n- **WHEN** a Patch operation is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL indicate invalid patch type\n\n### Requirement: Code Generation Automation\n\nThe system SHALL automate code generation to keep it in sync with CRD definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile generate target\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** `make gen-client` is executed\n- **THEN** client-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** informer-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** lister-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** all generated code SHALL be up to date\n\n#### Scenario: Code generation configuration\n- **GIVEN** the hack/update-codegen.sh script\n- **WHEN** the script is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL use k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1\n- **AND** it SHALL pass --with-watch flag\n- **AND** output package SHALL be github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n\n#### Scenario: CI code generation check\n- **GIVEN** a CI pipeline\n- **WHEN** code is committed\n- **THEN** the CI SHALL check if generated code is up to date\n- **AND** the CI SHALL fail if generated code is out of date\n\n#### Scenario: Regeneration preserves customizations\n- **GIVEN** existing generated code with custom modifications in non-generated files\n- **WHEN** code generation is run again\n- **THEN** generated files SHALL be regenerated\n- **AND** custom files SHALL not be modified\n- **AND** expansion hooks SHALL remain intact\n\n### Requirement: Testing\n\nThe system SHALL include comprehensive tests for all functionality.\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for client methods\n- **GIVEN** the client code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** all Create, Update, Get, List, Delete, Watch, Patch methods SHALL be tested\n- **AND** all error cases SHALL be tested\n- **AND** test coverage SHALL be at least 80%\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for informer\n- **GIVEN** the informer code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** informer initialization SHALL be tested\n- **AND** event handling SHALL be tested\n- **AND** cache operations SHALL be tested\n- **AND** synchronization SHALL be tested\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for lister\n- **GIVEN** the lister code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** list operations SHALL be tested\n- **AND** namespace filtering SHALL be tested\n- **AND** selector filtering SHALL be tested\n- **AND** O(1) lookup SHALL be verified\n\n#### Scenario: Integration tests\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** integration tests are run\n- **THEN** all client operations SHALL be tested against real cluster\n- **AND** watch functionality SHALL be tested\n- **AND** informer synchronization SHALL be tested\n- **AND** concurrent operations SHALL be tested\n\n#### Scenario: Fake client tests\n- **GIVEN** the fake clientset\n- **WHEN** fake client tests are run\n- **THEN** all operations SHALL work with in-memory storage\n- **AND** test assertions SHALL be supported\n- **AND** fake clients SHALL behave like real clients\n\n### Requirement: Documentation\n\nThe system SHALL include comprehensive documentation for all APIs.\n\n#### Scenario: README documentation\n- **GIVEN** the client-go repository\n- **WHEN** README.md is reviewed\n- **THEN** installation instructions SHALL be provided\n- **AND** basic usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** API reference SHALL be provided\n- **AND** module path SHALL be documented\n\n#### Scenario: API documentation\n- **GIVEN** the client API\n- **WHEN** documentation is reviewed\n- **THEN** all public methods SHALL be documented\n- **AND** all parameters SHALL be documented\n- **AND** all return values SHALL be documented\n- **AND** error cases SHALL be documented\n\n#### Scenario: Usage examples\n- **GIVEN** the examples directory\n- **WHEN** examples are reviewed\n- **THEN** clientset usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** informer usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** lister usage examples SHALL be provided\n\n#### Scenario: Go doc comments\n- **GIVEN** the generated code\n- **WHEN** Go doc is run\n- **THEN** all exported types SHALL have documentation\n- **AND** all exported functions SHALL have documentation\n- **AND** examples SHALL be provided where appropriate\n\n### Requirement: File Structure Completeness\n\nThe system SHALL include all required files in the client-go directory.\n\n#### Scenario: All clientset files exist\n- **GIVEN** the client-go directory\n- **WHEN** the clientset/versioned directory is listed\n- **THEN** clientset.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** scheme/register.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** scheme/doc.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/clientset_generated.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/register.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/doc.go SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: All typed client files exist\n- **GIVEN** the client-go directory\n- **WHEN** the clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1 directory is listed\n- **THEN** runtime_client.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** agentruntime.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** codeinterpreter.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** generated_expansion.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** doc.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/fake_runtime_client.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/fake_agentruntime.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** fake/doc.go SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: All informer files exist\n- **GIVEN** the client-go directory\n- **WHEN** the informers/externalversions directory is listed\n- **THEN** factory.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** generic.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** runtime/interface.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: All lister files exist\n- **GIVEN** the client-go directory\n- **WHEN** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1 directory is listed\n- **THEN** agentruntime.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** codeinterpreter.go SHALL exist\n- **AND** expansion_generated.go SHALL exist\n\n### Requirement: Source Reference Consistency\n\nThe system SHALL match the structure and behavior of the source reference at `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n#### Scenario: API group and version match\n- **GIVEN** the generated client\n- **WHEN** inspecting the API group and version\n- **THEN** the API group SHALL be runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n- **AND** the version SHALL be v1alpha1\n- **AND** this SHALL match the source reference\n\n#### Scenario: Module path matches\n- **GIVEN** the go.mod file\n- **WHEN** the module path is inspected\n- **THEN** the module path SHALL be github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n- **AND** this SHALL match the source reference\n\n#### Scenario: File structure matches\n- **GIVEN** the generated client\n- **WHEN** comparing to source reference\n- **THEN** all files SHALL match the source structure\n- **AND** all interfaces SHALL match the source interfaces\n- **AND** all types SHALL match the source types\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plurals match\n- **GIVEN** the generated client\n- **WHEN** inspecting resource plurals\n- **THEN** agentruntimes SHALL be the plural for AgentRuntime\n- **AND** codeinterpreters SHALL be the plural for CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** these SHALL match the source reference\n\n---\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThis delta specification defines a new Go module for the client-go client library. The module provides a new API for accessing AgentCube resources and does not affect existing deployments. Existing code using direct REST API calls can continue to work, but it is recommended to migrate to the typed client for better type safety and developer experience.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis delta specification depends on:\n- Go 1.19+\n- Kubernetes 1.20+\n- AR-001: Core API definitions (CRDs)\n- AR-002: AgentRuntime CRD definition\n- AR-003: CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n- k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/client-go\n- k8s.io/api\n- k8s.io/apimachinery\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines a new Go module that provides a client library. It does not break any existing functionality.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Authentication**: The client shall support all Kubernetes authentication methods (kubeconfig, service account tokens, TLS certificates).\n2. **Authorization**: The client shall respect Kubernetes RBAC policies and shall fail with appropriate errors when permissions are insufficient.\n3. **Secret Handling**: The client shall not log sensitive information such as tokens or passwords.\n4. **TLS Verification**: The client shall verify server TLS certificates by default.\n5. **Context Security**: The client shall respect context cancellation and timeouts to prevent resource leaks.\n6. **Input Validation**: The client shall validate inputs before sending to the API server.\n7. **Error Information**: The client shall not expose sensitive information in error messages.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Test all client methods (Create, Update, Get, List, Delete, Watch, Patch)\n- Test error handling for all error cases\n- Test informer initialization and event handling\n- Test lister operations and filtering\n- Test fake client functionality\n- Achieve at least 80% code coverage\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test all client operations against a real Kubernetes cluster\n- Test watch functionality with real events\n- Test informer synchronization\n- Test concurrent operations\n- Test with multiple Kubernetes versions\n\n### Performance Tests\n- Test CRUD operation latency\n- Test list operation latency with many resources\n- Test watch operation latency\n- Test informer cache synchronization time\n- Test memory usage with large numbers of resources\n\n### Compatibility Tests\n- Test against multiple Kubernetes versions (1.20, 1.21, 1.22, 1.23, 1.24)\n- Test with different API server configurations\n- Test with different authentication methods\n- Test with different Go versions\n\n### Regression Tests\n- Ensure code generation does not break existing functionality\n- Verify that regenerated code matches expected structure\n- Test that expansion hooks are preserved across regenerations\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\nThe client-go module shall be considered complete when:\n\n1. **Module Structure**: Go module is initialized with correct path and all required directories exist\n2. **Clientset**: All constructors and interfaces are properly implemented\n3. **Typed Clients**: Full CRUD operations for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter are available\n4. **Informers**: Event-driven workflows are supported through informers\n5. **Listers**: Efficient read-only access is provided through listers\n6. **Fake Clients**: Testing infrastructure is complete\n7. **Scheme**: All types are properly registered\n8. **Code Generation**: Automated code generation works correctly\n9. **Testing**: Comprehensive test coverage is achieved\n10. **Documentation**: Complete documentation and examples are provided\n11. **File Structure**: All required files are present and match source reference\n12. **API Compatibility**: Generated code matches the structure and behavior of the source reference","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887185557,"end":1775887185666}}}}
